* Projects
I have two major research projects underway, both in nonlinear physics and both with publishable papers in progress. Turns out that I have been slacking a bit on these recently and they are both in need of a bit more attention. One project is about the chaotic dynamics of a realistic billiard in a cone under constant gravitational acceleration. Another project is about a nonlinear system of {{{pde}}}s which models the dynamics of an infected respiratory tract, following parameters for both {{{diffusion}}} and {{{advection}}}. I hope to include some of my more detailed write-ups on these projects on this website soon.    

